<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09156f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09156f">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09156f"> 156(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mr Eyes (slams door / on guest)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Again: <mark>any chief who slams his village-gate on us and refuses to &ldquo;receive&rdquo; is also called Mr. Eyes</mark>. Ask them why, and they respond: &ldquo;The eyes receive no visitors; if even a speck of dust enters, they weep tears.&rdquo; A good description this of us two Missionaries, two specks of dust who, if they entered the town of Mr. Eyes, would make him weep. <small> Dan Crawford, <a name="BTLG1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BTLG1"><cite title="source">Back to the Long Grass</cite></a> (1923) 182</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
